# DREVORA CHANGE SAFETY RULES

- Modify only the feature explicitly requested.
- First identify the exact active route and rendered component.
- Do not edit duplicate, old, unused, backup or landing files unless the request specifically concerns the landing page.
- Inspect the existing services and live Supabase schema before changing data logic.
- Do not guess table names, column names, enum values or route paths.
- Preserve all existing working behaviour not explicitly requested to change.
- Do not delete, reset or recreate existing production data.
- Do not change the database schema unless explicitly required.
- Database changes must use a safe, idempotent SQL migration.
- Preserve existing record IDs and historical relationships.
- Do not create duplicate components, templates, companies or records.
- Reuse existing shared components, services and filtering logic.
- Keep company and tenant isolation applied.
- Never expose Supabase service-role or secret keys in frontend, VITE variables, GitHub or output.
- Run the application and verify the changed feature locally.
- Run a build after code changes.
- Perform regression checks for protected existing behaviour.
- Report the exact files changed.
- Report every regression check as PASS, FAIL or NOT TESTED.
- Do not claim completion if required behaviour was not verified.
- Do not run destructive database commands or demo seed scripts automatically.
- Make one focused change at a time.

# VEHICLE CHECKS PROTECTED BEHAVIOUR

When modifying Vehicle Checks, preserve and verify:

- One active Basic DVSA template, without duplicates.
- All 27 DVSA walkaround items remain in the correct order.
- Every DVSA item retains its full guidance text.
- Company custom checklist items remain.
- Vehicle-category extra checks remain.
- OK, Defect and N/A controls remain functional.
- Defect notes and photos remain functional.
- Odometer and miles/km remain functional.
- Worker signature remains functional.
- Inspection start time, completion time and duration remain functional.
- Existing completed Vehicle Checks and historical results must not be changed or deleted.
- Worker Vehicle Check flow remains mobile-first.
- Offline support must not be removed.

# REQUIRED WORKFLOW

Before editing:
1. Identify the active route and rendered component.
2. Identify related services and database tables.
3. List protected existing behaviour.

After editing:
1. Run typecheck/build.
2. Test the requested change.
3. Test protected existing behaviour.
4. Report exact files changed.
5. Report PASS, FAIL or NOT TESTED for every check.
